#This guide is how to configured the SNMP Proxy
#The configuration is only applicable to Proxy Server

#On this example the Central Management is acting SNMP Proxy Server
NMS Server = 192.168.71.108
CM Server = 192.168.71.101
Remote Server1 = 192.168.71.110
Remote Server2 = 192.168.71.111

NMS Server <> CM Server
SNMP Version v2c
Community String: SynetcomProxy 

CM Server <> Remote Servers
SNMP Version v2c
Community String: SynetcomFM2 

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SNMP Proxy v2c
1. Go to EfficientIP Cli 
2. Go to /data1/etc/snmpd/
3. Create copy of custom.conf
# cp custom.conf custom.conf.back
4. Edit the custom.conf using vim
5. Add the follow below
# Inbound Access : Allow NMS Server
rocommunity SynetcomProxy 192.168.71.108

# Access Policy
access Mygroup1 "" any noauth exact all none none

# Proxy Rules Pointing to Remote Servers
proxy -v 2c -c SynetcomFM2 192.168.71.110 .1.3.6.1.4.1.50001 1.3.6            // 1.3.6 will omit to query to remote server1      
proxy -v 2c -c SynetcomFM2 192.168.71.111 .1.3.6.1.4.1.50002 1.3.6            // 1.3.6 will omit to query to remote server2
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Testing on NMS Server 
# snmpwalk -v 2c -c SynetcomProxy 192.168.71.101 .1.3.6.1.4.1.50001.1.2.1.1.5.0        // Return Value String of the Hostname

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



