#On this example the Central Management is acting SNMP Proxy Server with snmp v3 to the remote appliances

NMS Server = 192.168.71.108
CM Server = 192.168.71.101
Remote Server1 = 192.168.71.110
Remote Server2 = 192.168.71.111

NMS Server <> CM Server
SNMP Version v2c
Community String: SynetcomProxy 

CM <> Remote Server
SNMP Version v3
Authentication
User: ipmserver
level: auth
Key: PLDT-Pr1v@t3Snmp!
Algo: SHA256

Privacy
Key: PLDT-Pr1v@t3Snmp!
Protocol: AES256

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SNMP Proxy v3
1. Go to EfficientIP Cli 
2. Go to /data1/etc/snmpd/
3. Create copy of custom.conf
# cp custom.conf custom.conf.back
4. Edit the custom.conf using vim
5. Add the follow below
# Inbound Access : Allow NMS Server
rocommunity SynetcomProxy 192.168.71.108

# Access Policy
access Mygroup1 "" any noauth exact all none none

# Proxy Rules Pointing to Remote Servers
proxy -v 3 -u ipmserver -l authPriv -a SHA-256 -A 'PLDT-Pr1v@t3Snmp!' -x AES-256 -X 'PLDT-Pr1v@t3Snmp!' 192.168.71.110 .1.3.6.1.4.1.50001 1.3.6           // 1.3.6 will omit to query to remote server1
proxy -v 3 -u ipmserver -l authPriv -a SHA-256 -A 'PLDT-Pr1v@t3Snmp!' -x AES-256 -X 'PLDT-Pr1v@t3Snmp!' 192.168.71.111 .1.3.6.1.4.1.50002 1.3.6           // 1.3.6 will omit to query to remote server2
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Testing on NMS Server 
snmpwalk -v 3 -u ipmserver -l authPriv -a SHA-256 -A 'PLDT-Pr1v@t3Snmp!' -x AES-256 -X 'PLDT-Pr1v@t3Snmp!' 192.168.71.101 .1.3.6.1.4.1.50001.1.2.1.1.5.0   // Return Value String of the Hostname

